1
00:00:00,080 --> 00:00:01,456
Have you seen Tun?

2
00:00:01,456 --> 00:00:02,560
Didn't he tell you?

3
00:00:02,560 --> 00:00:04,360
He went out of town.

4
00:00:04,360 --> 00:00:05,937
He went to a beach in Aou's hometown.

5
00:00:05,937 --> 00:00:09,470
It seemed like I was surrounded by many people.

6
00:00:09,470 --> 00:00:12,220
But in fact, I had no one in my life.

7
00:00:12,220 --> 00:00:16,263
So I always thought, I wanted to wake up

8
00:00:16,263 --> 00:00:19,988
and see that someone was waiting for me.

9
00:00:19,988 --> 00:00:22,400
Can you be that person for me?

10
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:23,900
Sure.

11
00:00:28,990 --> 00:00:30,900
Pretty.

12
00:00:30,900 --> 00:00:33,360
Yes, it is pretty.

13
00:00:33,360 --> 00:00:36,300
And you're being too obsessed with the poster.

14
00:00:37,210 --> 00:00:39,040
Hey.

15
00:00:39,040 --> 00:00:40,163
Here.

16
00:00:40,163 --> 00:00:42,500
I just finished the poster.

17
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:44,210
What do you think?

18
00:00:44,210 --> 00:00:45,690
Damn!

19
00:00:45,690 --> 00:00:47,490
Nice.

20
00:00:48,190 --> 00:00:52,580
Of course, it is. Tess designed it himself.

21
00:00:52,580 --> 00:00:54,620
I don't want to compliment you two anymore.

22
00:00:54,620 --> 00:00:58,240
Show your love somewhere else. It stinks.

23
00:01:00,061 --> 00:01:01,950
How is the editing going?

24
00:01:01,950 --> 00:01:04,050
A lot better than I expected.

25
00:01:04,050 --> 00:01:07,280
The love scene got me biting my pillow.

26
00:01:07,280 --> 00:01:09,920
As if the screenwriters were so deep in love.

27
00:01:09,920 --> 00:01:11,470
Damn right!

28
00:01:11,470 --> 00:01:15,840
If you tell me to rewrite the script now, it'd be even deeper in love.

29
00:01:15,840 --> 00:01:18,020
Right, Tess?

30
00:01:18,020 --> 00:01:19,420
Right, my ass.

31
00:01:19,420 --> 00:01:22,060
Hey, the editing is almost done.

32
00:01:22,060 --> 00:01:24,560
Can you recommend any colorist to take on the job?

33
00:01:25,480 --> 00:01:27,920
There's just one person that comes to mind.

34
00:01:27,920 --> 00:01:29,620
Who?

35
00:01:47,950 --> 00:01:49,610
[Vice Versa]

36
00:02:35,770 --> 00:02:38,010
[Vice Versa]

37
00:02:40,991 --> 00:02:45,674
[Episode 10 - Pink]

38
00:02:51,160 --> 00:02:52,990
I bought you snacks.

39
00:02:52,990 --> 00:02:54,590
Okay.

40
00:02:56,400 --> 00:03:00,868
Wow! This scene's color grading is excellent.

41
00:03:01,370 --> 00:03:03,550
Are you in love or something?

42
00:03:03,550 --> 00:03:06,440
Go away. Don't distract me.

43
00:03:06,440 --> 00:03:08,080
I'm trying to focus.

44
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:09,610
Don't be so mean.

45
00:03:09,610 --> 00:03:12,190
I bought us our favorite snack.

46
00:03:12,190 --> 00:03:13,690
This.

47
00:03:14,480 --> 00:03:17,960
Oh, I'm working.

48
00:03:17,960 --> 00:03:19,660
Feed me.

49
00:03:22,640 --> 00:03:24,560
Aw! How cute!

50
00:03:24,560 --> 00:03:27,919
- You mean me?
- The film you're grading.

51
00:03:28,830 --> 00:03:32,760
You can't sleep at night if you don't get to bug me, can you?

52
00:03:33,580 --> 00:03:35,610
I'm kidding.

53
00:03:35,610 --> 00:03:40,952
You're actually cuter than the colors you're grading.

54
00:03:43,141 --> 00:03:46,968
When will I get to eat? I'm waiting.

55
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:01,044
I want a big bite.

56
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:08,760
What are you doing, Tun?

57
00:04:08,760 --> 00:04:10,440
Feeding you a snack.

58
00:04:10,440 --> 00:04:14,543
Feeding, my foot! You're making a mess.

59
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:18,920
Wait. What are you looking for?

60
00:04:18,920 --> 00:04:20,950
A napkin.

61
00:04:20,950 --> 00:04:22,650
No need.

62
00:04:33,140 --> 00:04:35,520
Softer than the one from the package.

63
00:04:40,960 --> 00:04:43,227
You've got something there, too.

64
00:04:43,227 --> 00:04:44,680
I've got what?

65
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:46,890
- Come here.
- I've got nothing.

66
00:04:46,890 --> 00:04:48,690
I have now.

67
00:04:50,300 --> 00:04:52,540
That's my boy.

68
00:04:52,540 --> 00:04:54,400
He's been here for a long time.

69
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:56,880
No one has shown an interest in adopting him yet?

70
00:04:56,880 --> 00:05:00,411
No. No one has.

71
00:05:03,660 --> 00:05:06,532
How are you? Did you miss me?

72
00:05:08,220 --> 00:05:10,680
I'll leave you two be. Be right back.

73
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:12,680
- Sure.
- Sure.

74
00:05:18,840 --> 00:05:22,830
We've been here many times, but don't know what to call him.

75
00:05:22,830 --> 00:05:26,856
Should... we name him?

76
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:31,483
We better not. Or we might get attached to him.

77
00:05:32,140 --> 00:05:34,940
Come on. Just for fun.

78
00:05:34,940 --> 00:05:37,070
He looks a bit silly.

79
00:05:37,070 --> 00:05:39,050
Should we call him Aou?

80
00:05:39,050 --> 00:05:41,200
Bastard.

81
00:05:41,200 --> 00:05:43,210
I think Fuse suits him better.

82
00:05:43,210 --> 00:05:47,560
Nah! It sounds too handsome, rich, and charming for him.

83
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:50,130
What confidence.

84
00:05:50,130 --> 00:05:53,310
We found him on the street. How about "On the Way?"

85
00:05:53,310 --> 00:05:54,560
On the Way isn't a name.

86
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:58,096
- Street?
- Too blunt.

87
00:05:58,096 --> 00:05:59,530
God Save?

88
00:05:59,530 --> 00:06:02,300
He's not saved by God. He's saved by you.

89
00:06:02,300 --> 00:06:04,676
That's true.

90
00:06:07,870 --> 00:06:09,380
- Lucky.
- My name is Fuse.

91
00:06:09,380 --> 00:06:12,051
I mean his name, not yours.

92
00:06:13,770 --> 00:06:15,872
Why Lucky though?

93
00:06:16,780 --> 00:06:18,330
Look at him.

94
00:06:18,330 --> 00:06:22,380
He got hit by a car, all covered in blood, but he managed to survive.

95
00:06:22,380 --> 00:06:25,912
I think the name fits him.

96
00:06:26,780 --> 00:06:29,067
Damn it!

97
00:06:29,067 --> 00:06:30,700
Did I just name him?

98
00:06:30,700 --> 00:06:32,400
Yeah.

99
00:06:33,248 --> 00:06:36,840
Now we're connected, Lucky.

100
00:06:39,824 --> 00:06:42,400
Actually, he's fully recovered.

101
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:44,100
Really?

102
00:06:46,830 --> 00:06:50,440
You said no one has confirmed to adopt him. Right?

103
00:06:50,440 --> 00:06:54,942
Many people reached out, but none of them has confirmed to do so.

104
00:06:56,300 --> 00:06:59,760
Can I adopt him then?

105
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:03,150
Really? That's wonderful.

106
00:07:03,150 --> 00:07:05,310
Have you named him yet?

107
00:07:05,310 --> 00:07:08,440
We're thinking of naming him Lucky.

108
00:07:08,440 --> 00:07:09,950
Nice name.

109
00:07:09,950 --> 00:07:12,240
Congrats.

110
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:14,480
I'll prepare the necessary things for you then.

111
00:07:14,480 --> 00:07:16,880
- Thank you.
- See you in a bit.

112
00:07:18,840 --> 00:07:21,168
Hi.

113
00:07:21,168 --> 00:07:24,890
You'll live with your new daddy.

114
00:07:24,890 --> 00:07:27,532
Live with me, Lucky.

115
00:07:27,532 --> 00:07:29,940
[Three weeks later]
[Romantic (Non) Comedy]

116
00:07:34,510 --> 00:07:36,936
I'm Kita.

117
00:07:36,936 --> 00:07:38,336
I'm Fuse.

118
00:07:43,984 --> 00:07:46,260
You guys are here?

119
00:07:46,260 --> 00:07:47,923
Someone is waiting to see you.

120
00:07:47,923 --> 00:07:49,523
There.

121
00:07:52,813 --> 00:07:54,560
Hey!

122
00:07:54,560 --> 00:07:56,896
- Hello, Dol.
- How cute.

123
00:07:56,896 --> 00:07:59,430
Congrats. Are you excited?

124
00:07:59,430 --> 00:08:00,990
So excited.

125
00:08:00,990 --> 00:08:02,625
My heart is bursting out of my chest.

126
00:08:02,625 --> 00:08:04,090
What an overstatement.

127
00:08:04,090 --> 00:08:05,457
- Seriously?
- Seriously.

128
00:08:05,457 --> 00:08:07,470
He couldn't even sleep last night.

129
00:08:07,470 --> 00:08:10,830
He called asking me to talk him to sleep all night.

130
00:08:10,830 --> 00:08:13,480
Too much information.

131
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:17,396
You guys are great. I'm so proud of you, you know?

132
00:08:18,330 --> 00:08:21,087
Guys, we are taking a group photo over there.

133
00:08:22,120 --> 00:08:24,430
- Will you excuse me, Dol?
- Of course.

134
00:08:24,430 --> 00:08:26,440
Go on.

135
00:08:26,440 --> 00:08:28,440
Hurry up!

136
00:09:16,010 --> 00:09:18,590
Are you still worried?

137
00:09:18,590 --> 00:09:20,098
Yeah.

138
00:09:20,098 --> 00:09:23,040
Everyone put in their best effort.

139
00:09:23,040 --> 00:09:26,464
I'm afraid it'd turn out bad and they...

140
00:09:28,380 --> 00:09:30,564
Don't go to that yet.

141
00:09:31,160 --> 00:09:35,400
Let's just enjoy the movie for now.

142
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:54,228
Thanks to all the cast and staff for bringing this movie this far.

143
00:09:55,040 --> 00:09:57,810
Especially, the Friend Credits group.

144
00:09:57,810 --> 00:10:00,290
They initiated this project.

145
00:10:00,290 --> 00:10:03,956
They raised their own funds and produced the movie themselves.

146
00:10:04,620 --> 00:10:08,300
Without them, this movie wouldn't have happened.

147
00:10:08,300 --> 00:10:11,528
All the credits go to them.

148
00:10:15,500 --> 00:10:17,920
Since Mr. Mek has said it,

149
00:10:17,920 --> 00:10:23,020
may I have someone from Friend Credits up here to talk about the movie?

150
00:10:23,020 --> 00:10:28,800
Can we get Mr. Tess, the producer, here to say something about it?

151
00:10:28,800 --> 00:10:30,488
Please.

152
00:10:34,250 --> 00:10:39,960
Go on. Be our representative.

153
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:43,560
Besides, I want to hear your speech.

154
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:46,080
- Go on.
- If you won't, I will.

155
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:48,120
You stay here.

156
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:51,260
Please give it up for Tess.

157
00:10:51,260 --> 00:10:53,560
Please.

158
00:11:06,420 --> 00:11:08,180
Hello.

159
00:11:10,572 --> 00:11:13,560
I don't know what to say.

160
00:11:13,560 --> 00:11:18,510
I just want to say that making a movie

161
00:11:18,510 --> 00:11:21,420
is miraculous to me.

162
00:11:21,420 --> 00:11:27,160
It can bring strangers together to spend an unknown amount of time.

163
00:11:27,160 --> 00:11:29,169
- Did I do well?
- You surely did.

164
00:11:29,169 --> 00:11:32,612
I'm sure you'll be famous because of this.

165
00:11:33,638 --> 00:11:35,670
When the movie ends,

166
00:11:35,670 --> 00:11:40,480
we become brothers, sisters, family,

167
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:43,440
and everything for each other.

168
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:45,508
Thank you to all of you,

169
00:11:45,508 --> 00:11:50,404
the staff, and the fans who have come to this event.

170
00:11:51,040 --> 00:11:56,270
Thanks to the one who always stays by my side every day.

171
00:11:56,270 --> 00:11:59,243
Look. You like the colors I did there?

172
00:12:00,330 --> 00:12:02,033
Do I still need to say?

173
00:12:02,033 --> 00:12:04,031
They are very beautiful.

174
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:15,100
Thank you.

175
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:36,190
Guys, whether our movie is a box office success or not,

176
00:12:36,190 --> 00:12:40,280
I'm glad we did our best to get it into theaters.

177
00:12:40,280 --> 00:12:41,500
Right.

178
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:46,404
You guys are the reason I want to live long and do what I love.

179
00:12:48,087 --> 00:12:53,939
And you guys make me realize what I actually love.

180
00:12:59,530 --> 00:13:01,150
Come on.

181
00:13:01,150 --> 00:13:03,210
It's just water, but cheers anyway!

182
00:13:03,210 --> 00:13:05,348
Cheers!

183
00:13:28,510 --> 00:13:30,600
What are you doing, Tun?

184
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:33,660
Cleaning your face. It's a mess.

185
00:13:33,660 --> 00:13:36,110
Why now?

186
00:13:36,110 --> 00:13:38,780
You can do it at home.

187
00:13:38,780 --> 00:13:40,810
I've prepared it for you.

188
00:13:40,810 --> 00:13:43,828
As I know we have lots to do today.

189
00:14:02,160 --> 00:14:05,100
It's such a long day for you.

190
00:14:05,100 --> 00:14:07,660
And with all the dust,

191
00:14:08,360 --> 00:14:10,380
we should wipe it off right away.

192
00:14:13,280 --> 00:14:14,970
Why?

193
00:14:14,970 --> 00:14:19,052
You can't take it when I look bad just for a second?

194
00:14:20,400 --> 00:14:21,960
It's not that.

195
00:14:21,960 --> 00:14:25,224
I'm not cleaning it because I'm afraid you'd look bad.

196
00:14:26,190 --> 00:14:28,372
I just want to take care of you.

197
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:56,200
Thank you...

198
00:14:57,040 --> 00:14:59,492
for cleaning my face,

199
00:15:00,480 --> 00:15:02,280
and for...

200
00:15:03,710 --> 00:15:06,072
cleaning off my dusty heart.

201
00:15:07,070 --> 00:15:09,752
It's now back in use again.

202
00:15:18,170 --> 00:15:20,070
Aou!

203
00:15:21,360 --> 00:15:22,737
Is there any stain on my face?

204
00:15:22,737 --> 00:15:24,920
Where? Let me see.

205
00:15:24,920 --> 00:15:26,120
Right here, my friend.

206
00:15:26,120 --> 00:15:27,296
- Here?
- Yes.

207
00:15:27,296 --> 00:15:29,300
Let me wipe it for you.

208
00:15:29,980 --> 00:15:32,680
Aou, can you wipe away the dust in my heart?

209
00:15:32,680 --> 00:15:36,730
- Why?
- I want to bring it back to life.

210
00:15:36,730 --> 00:15:39,001
Let me clean it for you.

211
00:15:40,410 --> 00:15:44,140
Hey, I can't hide my excitement.

212
00:15:44,140 --> 00:15:47,120
I didn't expect many people to love our movie.

213
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:48,480
Don't speak too soon.

214
00:15:48,480 --> 00:15:51,550
Wait until you read the critiques from the movie review pages.

215
00:15:51,550 --> 00:15:55,200
It will turn out fine. Trust me.

216
00:15:55,200 --> 00:15:58,750
The script you wrote is great.

217
00:15:58,750 --> 00:16:02,540
No. It's because your color grading is great.

218
00:16:02,540 --> 00:16:04,560
Because your dialogues are heartfelt.

219
00:16:04,560 --> 00:16:07,002
Can I get a reward from you then?

220
00:16:08,480 --> 00:16:09,960
What do you want?

221
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:13,870
Can I use your bathtub tonight?

222
00:16:13,870 --> 00:16:15,340
Sure.

223
00:16:15,340 --> 00:16:17,368
I'm not done.

224
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:20,690
Can I use it with you?

225
00:16:20,690 --> 00:16:22,570
Tun, you asshole.

226
00:16:22,570 --> 00:16:25,936
What? You already agreed to it. Don't break your word.

227
00:16:25,936 --> 00:16:27,740
No!

228
00:16:30,090 --> 00:16:32,570
I missed your bathtub so much.

229
00:16:32,570 --> 00:16:34,018
Take a bath only.

230
00:16:34,018 --> 00:16:37,420
Of course. What else do you think I'll do?

231
00:16:37,420 --> 00:16:39,656
Be quiet.

232
00:16:40,277 --> 00:16:42,110
I can't be.

233
00:16:42,110 --> 00:16:44,910
Because I'm reading the movie feedback on the pages.

234
00:16:44,910 --> 00:16:47,200
Let's read it together.

235
00:16:47,200 --> 00:16:48,750
I left my phone outside.

236
00:16:48,750 --> 00:16:50,060
Let me go grab it.

237
00:16:50,060 --> 00:16:52,100
Hey.

238
00:16:52,100 --> 00:16:55,067
No need. Read it with me.

239
00:17:02,267 --> 00:17:03,440
Look.

240
00:17:03,440 --> 00:17:06,890
Nung Tid Mun says that the movie has an interesting point.

241
00:17:06,890 --> 00:17:09,240
How the story is told differs from other movies.

242
00:17:09,240 --> 00:17:10,883
The romantic scene is fulfilling.

243
00:17:10,883 --> 00:17:13,459
We get 10 out of 10.

244
00:17:17,240 --> 00:17:20,040
It says here that the movie has a little dark comedy.

245
00:17:20,040 --> 00:17:21,930
9 out of 10.

246
00:17:21,930 --> 00:17:23,792
Damn!

247
00:17:23,792 --> 00:17:28,510
Movie Seer says the characters and how we present the story are both outstanding.

248
00:17:28,510 --> 00:17:31,390
It's an up-and-coming Thai movie of the year.

249
00:17:31,390 --> 00:17:35,470
The screenwriters have done a much better job than in their last movie.

250
00:17:35,470 --> 00:17:36,863
10 out of 10.

251
00:17:36,863 --> 00:17:39,080
Holy shit!

252
00:17:39,080 --> 00:17:42,568
We won Khai and Third's hearts.

253
00:17:54,680 --> 00:17:57,240
You just rewarded me.

254
00:17:57,240 --> 00:18:00,144
Can I reward you back?

255
00:18:02,090 --> 00:18:04,252
What is my reward?

256
00:18:41,230 --> 00:18:43,992
Thank you for everything.

257
00:18:46,330 --> 00:18:48,852
Thank you, too.

258
00:19:22,480 --> 00:19:24,640
Lucky, come here. Good boy.

259
00:19:24,640 --> 00:19:26,574
I thought I adopted only one.

260
00:19:26,574 --> 00:19:28,440
When did that become two?

261
00:19:28,440 --> 00:19:31,300
Do you want to get bitten?

262
00:19:31,300 --> 00:19:32,620
Lucky, come to Daddy.

263
00:19:32,620 --> 00:19:34,510
Don't play with this aggressive dog.

264
00:19:34,510 --> 00:19:37,000
Well, well.

265
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:40,350
It's good you adopted Lucky.

266
00:19:40,350 --> 00:19:43,820
You know I wanted to have a dog as a kid.

267
00:19:43,820 --> 00:19:47,340
I wanted to take my pet everywhere with me.

268
00:19:47,340 --> 00:19:49,400
But my dad wouldn't allow me to do it.

269
00:19:49,400 --> 00:19:50,460
What a shame.

270
00:19:50,460 --> 00:19:52,033
- Whatever!
- What?

271
00:19:52,033 --> 00:19:54,590
Who would want to take their pet everywhere?

272
00:19:54,590 --> 00:19:56,090
A lot of people.

273
00:19:56,090 --> 00:19:59,160
I have an example here. You!

274
00:19:59,160 --> 00:20:00,490
You asked me to drag you everywhere.

275
00:20:00,490 --> 00:20:02,540
No! I take you everywhere.

276
