I wished for our movie to be shown at the Kannes Film Festival.

553
00:39:30,890 --> 00:39:35,640
And it was a success!

554
00:39:37,840 --> 00:39:40,532
Mine is right here.

555
00:39:42,680 --> 00:39:46,268
My wish was...

556
00:39:47,280 --> 00:39:49,870
to get a dog.

557
00:39:49,870 --> 00:39:51,420
Wait.

558
00:39:51,420 --> 00:39:53,210
When did you even have a dog, Aou?

559
00:39:53,210 --> 00:39:54,576
He's Fuse's dog.

560
00:39:54,576 --> 00:39:56,500
He has one in his mouth.

561
00:39:56,500 --> 00:39:58,170
Damn you.

562
00:39:58,170 --> 00:40:01,000
He's like my dog.

563
00:40:01,000 --> 00:40:03,790
I'm the one taking care of the dog.

564
00:40:05,000 --> 00:40:08,510
- What?
- What's stuck in your throat?

565
00:40:08,510 --> 00:40:11,112
Tess, what's your wish?

566
00:40:21,320 --> 00:40:24,068
I wished to find the port...

567
00:40:28,300 --> 00:40:30,128
Someone I like.

568
00:40:31,136 --> 00:40:35,320
And I've found him.

569
00:40:37,900 --> 00:40:39,870
Gosh! People in love stink.

570
00:40:39,870 --> 00:40:42,470
- Let's skip to Tun.
- Right.

571
00:40:42,470 --> 00:40:46,380
Tun has just one wish there.

572
00:40:46,380 --> 00:40:47,780
Go.

573
00:41:00,560 --> 00:41:04,056
Mine has already come true as well.

574
00:41:06,650 --> 00:41:09,280
Aren't you gonna say what you wished for?

575
00:41:09,280 --> 00:41:10,920
Don't break the rule.

576
00:41:10,920 --> 00:41:12,900
Tell us.

577
00:41:12,900 --> 00:41:14,670
I won't.

578
00:41:14,670 --> 00:41:17,350
Tess is the only one allowed to know.

579
00:41:19,960 --> 00:41:22,220
They've got a secret.

580
00:41:22,220 --> 00:41:23,610
Guys.

581
00:41:23,610 --> 00:41:26,247
Pan-grilled pork is ready. Let's celebrate.

582
00:41:26,247 --> 00:41:28,689
Pan-grilled pork?

583
00:41:28,689 --> 00:41:30,190
What is it?

584
00:41:30,190 --> 00:41:31,850
I didn't know it either at first.

585
00:41:31,850 --> 00:41:35,340
But Tess said it was traditional food of a tribe overseas.

586
00:41:35,340 --> 00:41:38,650
We grill the pork on a pan until it's cooked.

587
00:41:38,650 --> 00:41:40,400
Then we dip it in a sauce.

588
00:41:40,400 --> 00:41:41,820
It's so good.

589
00:41:41,820 --> 00:41:43,520
Try it.

590
00:41:44,760 --> 00:41:46,093
You lied to them.

591
00:41:46,093 --> 00:41:48,651
It isn't tribal food.

592
00:41:49,480 --> 00:41:53,136
I couldn't say it's food from the other universe, could I?

593
00:41:53,920 --> 00:41:55,520
Right.

594
00:41:55,520 --> 00:41:59,200
Guys, let's go. I'm starving.

595
00:42:00,032 --> 00:42:01,680
Come on. Time to eat.

596
00:42:01,680 --> 00:42:04,010
Pan-grilled pork is so good. Trust me.

597
00:42:04,010 --> 00:42:06,216
Pan-grilled pork?

598
00:42:16,720 --> 00:42:19,904
I had no idea there was a thing called pan-grilled pork in this world.

599
00:42:19,904 --> 00:42:21,290
It's freaking good.

600
00:42:21,290 --> 00:42:23,920
Can we make it again some other time?

601
00:42:23,920 --> 00:42:27,304
I'm afraid we won't get the chance to do so.

602
00:42:31,560 --> 00:42:33,120
Why not?

603
00:42:33,120 --> 00:42:38,920
I just feel like we're growing up every day.

604
00:42:39,740 --> 00:42:44,248
We have our dreams and burdens to handle.

605
00:42:45,240 --> 00:42:48,676
We might not get a chance to gather like this again.

606
00:42:49,660 --> 00:42:55,092
When that day comes, will you be okay?

607
00:42:58,520 --> 00:43:00,640
It'll be sad.

608
00:43:00,640 --> 00:43:04,570
I don't know if we get a chance

609
00:43:04,570 --> 00:43:07,580
to do anything like this again.

610
00:43:08,140 --> 00:43:10,490
I just want you all to know

611
00:43:10,490 --> 00:43:14,160
no matter how much time passes,

612
00:43:14,160 --> 00:43:18,436
the memories we have today will remain.

613
00:43:21,280 --> 00:43:26,190
I just hope, in the future, when you guys look back,

614
00:43:26,190 --> 00:43:30,852
you will see us when we're happy together, just like today.

615
00:43:40,640 --> 00:43:42,003
Clearly.

616
00:43:42,003 --> 00:43:44,983
Are you quitting this job for good?

617
00:43:45,580 --> 00:43:48,292
It sounds like a farewell.

618
00:43:50,110 --> 00:43:52,348
It isn't a farewell.

619
00:43:53,210 --> 00:43:55,624
I'll be just right here, always.

620
00:43:58,420 --> 00:44:00,320
And forever.

621
00:44:05,360 --> 00:44:07,790
I love you all.

622
00:44:07,790 --> 00:44:10,880
I don't know if that's a farewell or not.

623
00:44:10,880 --> 00:44:12,860
But it's damn touching.

624
00:44:12,860 --> 00:44:16,760
Guys. Group hug.

625
00:44:22,300 --> 00:44:23,660
I love you all.

626
00:44:23,660 --> 00:44:27,956
I love you all!

627
00:44:29,580 --> 00:44:31,892
Cheers!

628
00:44:58,380 --> 00:45:00,784
Are you secretly crying here all alone?

629
00:45:01,600 --> 00:45:03,780
No.

630
00:45:03,780 --> 00:45:05,972
I've just got dust in my eyes.

631
00:45:12,160 --> 00:45:14,820
You're such a bad liar.

632
00:45:14,820 --> 00:45:16,880
If the stars have their own color,

633
00:45:25,710 --> 00:45:30,776
what color should they each have?

634
00:45:35,300 --> 00:45:37,480
I can't think of it.

635
00:45:39,264 --> 00:45:42,160
But the color that stands out to me...

636
00:45:44,670 --> 00:45:49,120
is the one you asked me to name in Rawi's Palette color system.

637
00:45:49,120 --> 00:45:51,740
Have you heard of Pantone?

638
00:45:51,740 --> 00:45:53,770
The color matching system?

639
00:45:53,770 --> 00:45:54,837
Right.

640
00:45:54,837 --> 00:45:59,371
I like to see people through Pantone colors.

641
00:46:00,760 --> 00:46:01,963
What about me?

642
00:46:01,963 --> 00:46:03,763
I don't know.

643
00:46:07,600 --> 00:46:10,496
What should we name this color system?

644
00:46:11,690 --> 00:46:13,820
Rawi.

645
00:46:13,820 --> 00:46:15,740
How about Rawi's Palette?

646
00:46:15,740 --> 00:46:17,340
Rawi's Palette?

647
00:46:17,340 --> 00:46:21,128
The color system you invented.

648
00:46:24,490 --> 00:46:27,064
I now can think of the color.

649
00:46:28,770 --> 00:46:30,676
Its first color.

650
00:46:31,720 --> 00:46:34,880
Really? What color?

651
00:46:35,950 --> 00:46:40,960
It's the color that makes me feel the longing...

652
00:46:42,110 --> 00:46:44,220
and the warmth.

653
00:46:48,510 --> 00:46:53,404
Sometimes it makes me feel love.

654
00:46:56,420 --> 00:46:58,468
Pink.

655
00:46:59,560 --> 00:47:01,360
Our color.

656
00:47:02,460 --> 00:47:04,160
Right.

657
00:47:05,560 --> 00:47:10,060
I named this color "Shy".

658
00:47:12,670 --> 00:47:14,852
Why did you call it that?

659
00:47:16,490 --> 00:47:20,708
Because sometimes it's shy,

660
00:47:22,600 --> 00:47:24,980
but so damn cute.

661
00:47:29,480 --> 00:47:32,060
You mean you or me?

662
00:47:37,760 --> 00:47:40,072
Thank you so much though.

663
00:47:40,970 --> 00:47:43,532
I love the name a lot.

664
00:47:52,350 --> 00:47:57,136
All of a sudden, I feel like I'm an important person in this world.

665
00:47:57,940 --> 00:47:59,944
You're exaggerating.

666
00:48:10,090 --> 00:48:13,968
Do you remember the movie's ending scene we talked about?

667
00:48:14,850 --> 00:48:16,550
Of course, I do.

668
00:48:31,770 --> 00:48:37,624
What do think our ending will be like?

669
00:48:39,300 --> 00:48:43,204
Everyone wants a happy ending.

670
00:48:44,357 --> 00:48:51,947
But I think life isn't that easy.

671
00:48:52,860 --> 00:48:55,760
What you said is right.

672
00:48:55,760 --> 00:49:01,860
Even so, I like the dialogue in our movie's ending scene anyway.

673
00:49:06,850 --> 00:49:09,944
"Though we aren't together tomorrow,

674
00:49:10,820 --> 00:49:14,784
you're always here in my memories."

675
00:49:31,230 --> 00:49:34,820
♫ There's only you here, I'm not going anywhere ♫

676
00:49:34,820 --> 00:49:38,360
♫ With you right here by my side ♫

677
00:49:38,360 --> 00:49:43,930
♫ Forever, not expecting anything more than this ♫

678
00:49:43,930 --> 00:49:53,570
♫ There's only you here. Whatever happens, I won't be afraid ♫

679
00:49:53,570 --> 00:49:59,170
♫ Just having you here by my side ♫

680
00:50:01,710 --> 00:50:06,524
I don't know when we will get to go home.

681
00:50:09,480 --> 00:50:12,520
But no matter where you'll be,

682
00:50:12,520 --> 00:50:17,656
I promise I'll look for you.

683
00:50:27,210 --> 00:50:30,010
If I tell you my name,

684
00:50:30,010 --> 00:50:34,892
will you promise to name my color?

685
00:50:37,610 --> 00:50:40,800
Before we go back,

686
00:50:40,800 --> 00:50:43,640
I want you to know my real name.

687
00:50:43,640 --> 00:50:47,020
Maybe you can find me first.

688
00:50:47,020 --> 00:50:48,720
My name is...

689
00:51:25,200 --> 00:51:29,720
Tun. Tun. Tun. Tun.

690
00:51:29,720 --> 00:51:31,210
I dreamed.

691
00:51:31,210 --> 00:51:32,860
Shit! I just dreamed.

692
00:51:32,860 --> 00:51:34,980
We're going home.

693
00:51:34,980 --> 00:51:36,680
Tun!

694
00:51:44,720 --> 00:51:46,170
Holy shit!

695
00:51:46,170 --> 00:51:48,930
I dreamed too, Tess!

696
00:51:48,930 --> 00:51:51,620
We're finally back in our universe.

697
00:52:05,740 --> 00:52:07,622
What?

698
00:52:07,622 --> 00:52:09,522
Don't tell me...

699
00:52:11,730 --> 00:52:13,656
you're Pakorn.

700
00:52:17,840 --> 00:52:21,780
Yes, I am Pakorn.

701
00:52:34,330 --> 00:52:36,576
Are you Talay?

702
00:52:43,550 --> 00:52:45,804
That means...

703
00:52:47,900 --> 00:52:51,064
You and Tess aren't back home yet.

704
00:53:42,800 --> 00:53:45,260
Hey! This too.

705
00:53:45,260 --> 00:53:47,776
It tastes just like when I was filming in our universe.

706
00:53:47,776 --> 00:53:50,416
Mafia the Movie, Scene 2, Cut 1, Take 1.

707
00:53:50,416 --> 00:53:53,128
And... action.

708
00:53:54,128 --> 00:54:00,888
I remember I made all the crew's mouths water.

709
00:54:06,320 --> 00:54:08,420
Poor them.

710
00:54:08,420 --> 00:54:11,584
You're such a cruel actor.

711
00:54:11,584 --> 00:54:16,016
I'll not share it with you anymore then.

712
00:54:16,016 --> 00:54:18,810
I'm doing this for that crew.

713
00:54:34,640 --> 00:54:36,496
Are you sulking?

714
00:55:52,060 --> 00:55:54,960
If I get to go back to that universe,

715
00:55:54,960 --> 00:55:57,195
I will miss this universe so much.

716
00:56:17,390 --> 00:56:19,310
Tun hasn't told me his real name.

717
00:56:19,310 --> 00:56:21,310
Do you know his name?

718
00:56:21,310 --> 00:56:24,000
I think he's trying to tell you.

719
00:56:24,000 --> 00:56:25,920
Just like Dol said.

720
00:56:25,920 --> 00:56:29,850
You must dream and go to that placein order to return.

721
00:56:29,850 --> 00:56:31,870
I finally found you.

722
00:56:31,870 --> 00:56:34,210
What the heck are you doing, Pakorn?

723
00:56:36,080 --> 00:56:37,950
Are you Tess?

724
00:56:37,950 --> 00:56:39,298
Yes.

725
00:56:39,298 --> 00:56:41,098
Tess.

726
00:56:42,730 --> 00:56:49,200
♫ I want you to trust me and hold onto my hand ♫

727
00:56:49,200 --> 00:56:54,440
♫ From now on, the path we take is ours ♫

728
00:56:54,440 --> 00:57:01,200
♫ It's because of you that gave today meaning ♫

729
00:57:01,200 --> 00:57:10,740
♫ And you just made me learn my own worth ♫

730
00:57:10,740 --> 00:57:14,550
♫ There's only you here, I'm not going anywhere ♫

731
00:57:14,550 --> 00:57:18,150
♫ With you right here by my side ♫

732
00:57:18,150 --> 00:57:23,650
♫ Forever, not expecting anything more than this ♫

733
00:57:23,650 --> 00:57:32,790
♫ There's only you here. Whatever happens, I won't be afraid ♫

734
00:57:32,790 --> 00:57:39,750
♫ Just having you here by my side ♫
